Security: Add SSRF host validation to external storage backend configuration

The external storage controller accepted arbitrary host values for
network-capable backends such as WebDAV without validating against
private IP ranges, loopback, or link-local addresses. When user
storage mounting was enabled, any authenticated user could force the
server to make HTTP requests to cloud metadata endpoints or internal
services. Validation now blocks RFC-1918, loopback, link-local, and
equivalent IPv6 ranges, with an admin opt-out for legitimate internal
storage.

